It was a Cornish Miner,

                     Heylin's Geography. That Discovered the Tin Mines in Saxony, Violet, and Stevens;

                     Lex Mercat. 169. and the Tombstones of said Violet and Stevens, at Enckhuysen, till demolished in the first Dutch Wars, by the Rabble. Two discontented English Fishmongers setling at Enckhuysen in Holland, first taught us to make deep Sea Nets, and Fish upon the Brittish Coasts. And indeed few People venture to Travel, who are not Masters of some excellent Arts or Sciences. But put chance any Poor visited us, who had no Trades in their Bellies; if they will not serve us for Soldiers, yet they'll serve to make Bricks, dig Turff, &c.
